{"title":"Local Descriptors Optimized for Average Precision","domain":"CV","seeds":[{"problem":"Learning-based local feature descriptors are typically trained with pairwise/triplet surrogate losses that do not directly optimize the nearest-neighbor matching stage, leading to suboptimal ranking performance and reliance on hard-negative mining heuristics.","method":"Model descriptor matching as nearest-neighbor retrieval and train deep networks to directly optimize the listwise metric Average Precision (AP). Implement differentiable AP optimization via histogram-binning approximations: for binary descriptors, use smoothed Hamming-distance histograms with tanh-thresholded bits; for real-valued descriptors, introduce a quantization-based approximation by binning Euclidean distances of L2-normalized descriptors over [0,2], enabling end-to-end gradients. This listwise optimization is position-sensitive, removes the need for complex mining heuristics, and achieves state-of-the-art on UBC Phototour, HPatches, RomePatches, and Oxford image matching."},{"problem":"Geometric noise (e.g., rotation, scale, affine distortions) in local patches degrades descriptor robustness and matching accuracy.","method":"Augment the descriptor network with a Spatial Transformer that predicts a 6-DOF affine transform to align input patches without extra supervision. Mitigate out-of-boundary sampling artifacts by replicate boundary padding instead of zero padding, stabilizing alignment for small patch inputs. The resulting DOAP-ST variant consistently improves over the base descriptor across benchmarks."},{"problem":"In HPatches, image matching involves in-sequence distractors that are not modeled when training on patch retrieval with only out-of-sequence negatives, causing a train-test mismatch and reduced matching performance.","method":"Mine additional in-sequence distractor labels via clustering within each sequence using HOG+raw-pixel features and K-means; treat cluster pairs with inter-cluster distance above a threshold (with 3D verification) as distractors. Modify minibatch sampling to draw two sequences per batch to include many in-sequence negatives. This label-mined DOAP-ST-LM significantly boosts image matching mAP on HPatches (e.g., ≈+6% over DOAP-ST and ≈+10% over L2Net), including tough cases."}]}
